## 13. ERROR HANDLING & EDGE CASES

### 13.1 Error Scenarios

| Scenario | Handling Strategy |
|----------|-------------------|
| Invalid GitHub URL | Show inline validation error, suggest format |
| Private repository | Display "Repository not accessible" message |
| Rate limit exceeded | Show retry timer, suggest authentication |
| Parsing failure | Fall back to generic parser, show low confidence |
| Network timeout | Retry with exponential backoff, show progress |
| Empty repository | Display "No files found" message |
| Unsupported language | Use generic fallback, show warning |

### 13.2 Graceful Degradation

```typescript
try {
  const parsed = await parserService.parse(metadata, repoType);
  return parsed;
} catch (error) {
  console.error("Parsing failed:", error);
  
  // Attempt fallback parsing
  try {
    return await parserService.parseFallback(metadata);
  } catch (fallbackError) {
    // Return minimal structure
    return {
      metadata,
      nodes: generateMinimalNodes(metadata),
      dependencies: [],
      layers: generateDefaultLayers(),
      storySteps: [],
      confidence: 20
    };
  }
}
```

